{"id":"296634558_Beyond_the_Fold_Emerging_Biological_Applications_of_DNA_Origami","abstract":"The use of DNA as a material for nanoscale construction has exploded in the past decade. This is largely attributable to the DNA origami technique, which has enabled construction of nanostructures ranging from simple two-dimensional sheets to complex three-dimensional objects with defined curvatures and edges. These structures are amenable to site-specific functionalization with nanometer level precision, and have been shown to exhibit some cellular biocompatibility and permeability. The DNA origami technique has already found widespread use in a variety of emerging biological applications such as biosensing, enzyme cascades, biomolecular analysis, biomimetics, and drug delivery. This Minireview highlights a few of these applications and comments on the prospects of this rapidly expanding field of research.","authors":["Arun Richard Chandrasekaran","Nate Anderson","Megan Kizer","Ken Halvorsen"],"meta":["March 2016ChemBioChem 17(12)","DOI:10.1002/cbic.201600038","Project: DNA nanostructures and their applications in biology and medicine"],"references":["284184474_Daunorubicin-Loaded_DNA_Origami_Nanostructures_Circumvent_Drug-Resistance_Mechanisms_in_a_Leukemia_Model","281636549_G-quadruplexes_and_their_regulatory_roles_in_biology","277785099_Monitoring_Patterned_Enzymatic_Polymerization_on_DNA_Origami_at_Single-molecule_level","276208305_Purification_of_Functionalized_DNA_Origami_Nanostructures","274258404_Dynamic_DNA_devices_and_assemblies_formed_by_shape-complementary_non-base_pairing_3D_components","270963104_DNA_nanotechnology_for_nanophotonic_applications","270832551_A_modular_DNA_origami-based_enzyme_cascade_nanoreactor","270651718_Programmable_Motion_of_DNA_Origami_Mechanisms","269287300_Isothermal_DNA_Origami_folding_Avoiding_denaturing_conditions_for_one-pot_hybrid-component_annealing","269284504_DNA_Nanoswitches_A_Quantitative_Platform_for_Gel-Based_Biomolecular_In